THE SPECTRE: CRIMES AND PUNISHMENT is a thought-provoking book that uses a super-powered entity to explore philosophical and theological issues of morality. Retold and redefined in this volume is the origin of the Spectre, the most powerful being in the universe. As the Wrath of God bonded on a human soul, the Spectre roams the Earth in order to confront evil and avenge the unavenged dead as a form of penance. Paying for his earthly sins, the Spectre must not only oppose evil but also understand why men commit it. Once this metaphysical journey is completed, his mortal soul will be freed and another will be called upon on this holy mission of redemption. - DC Comics.com
name: Crimes and Punishments

description: The X-Men arrive in Washington and witness the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants - Pyro, Avalanche, and the Blob - launch their attack. Meanwhile, Gambit manages to escape from Wolverine and Bishop, following the other X-Men to Washington, with Wolverine and Bishop on his tail. The X-Men defeat Pyro, Blob and Avalanche, but neither Gambit or Robert Kelly - the supposed assassin and his victim - are anywhere in sight.

The Brotherhood of Evil Mutants creates a distraction, destroying a building. While the X-Men save the people, their enemies escape. Meanwhile, Mystique, imitating Gambit, is ready to kill Senator Kelly, but she's stopped by timely arrival of the real Gambit.

As Bishop finds the two Gambits, he's more than happy to shoot them both just to make sure. However, Rogue sends him back to the future by breaking his temporal transponder. Mystique confesses that she's really Rogue's adoptive mother and wanted Rogue to join Apocalypse so that they could be together. Rogue allows Mystique to leave.

As Bishop finds himself in his own time again, he's surprised to see that nothing changed, except Wolverine is dead, with only his adamantium skeleton remaining. Forge supposes that Bishop would need to return to the past once more and finish his job.

The problem is that Senator Kelly is kidnapped by Magneto. Professor X uses Cerebro to detect Magneto's lair and sends the X-Men to rescue Kelly, knowing that this is the only way to change the future.

Magneto is going to kill Senator Kelly in order to start a conflict between humans and mutants. He's interrupted by arrival of Sentinels who rescue Kelly and leave Magneto unconscious and wounded. Kelly is brought to Bolivar Trask's base, where Master Mold produces more and more Sentinels. Trask offers an alliance which Kelly gladly accepts, but then Master Mold proclaims that from now on, he's giving the orders, and decides to replace Kelly's brain with a computer and later repeat this procedure with other influential politics.

The X-Men attack Agent Gyrich and get information about the Sentinels' base from him. They decide to attack the base and rescue Kelly, even though bitter Magneto warns them against it.

The issue - and the series - end with a cliffhanger, showing the X-Men launching their attack on the Sentinels' base.
A most excellent movie adaptation!

description:
An immortal warrior traveling through time, John Prophet is prematurely awakened from his cryogenic sleep only to find himself at the mercy of the mysterious Omen and the dark forces of his disciples. Communicating with an orbital satellite that relays all vital information and geared with a personal arsenal Prophet is perhaps the most dangerous soldier on the face of the planet. Now deep within the heart of a terrifying military installation known as Ragnarok, Prophet and his ally Kirby must fight not only for their own survival but the fate of all Mankind.

The only living native of the world they discover is a feral human/zombie hybrid dubbed Patient X! Can our trio elude the brawling natures of Patient X and Kurtis Kasey, plus a massive laboratory filled with super strong and super agile zombies long enough to make the jump to the next dimension?!

After a few misunderstandings to feel each other out, they soon discover Jamie and Britt lost within the deadly woods on Violets property! Can Violet's crash course in magic give Paige the ability to save her friends from zombies, Kurtis, Patient X, and huge poisonous spiders?!

description: Get ready for Rod Espinosas incredible adaptation of this timeless classic. The Eisner-nominated creator of such critically acclaimed, sweeping epics as Neotopia and Courageous Princess applies his visionary hand to Lewis Carroll's time-honored tale of an adventurous young girl who is swept into a strange magical fantasyland. Is it real or a dream? Journey down the rabbit hole in this amazing, lavishly illustrated, full color mini-series that is destined to become a new classic!
name: Down the Rabbit Hole

description: Marvel's most-requested duo return in this all-new one-shot, spinning out of X-MEN: NATION X! Cloak -- dark, brooding teleporter. Dagger -- deadly, shining mistress of light. Having quit the Dark X-Men, Cloak and Dagger find their partnership strained as they struggle to fit in among the mutants of Utopia. But when a new menace targets Cloak, Dagger must make a fateful choice for both of them. Guest-starring the X-Men, and written by Stuart Moore (WOLVERINE NOIR) with stunning art by Mark Brooks (YOUNG AVENGERS).
name: The Broken Church

description: After nearly drowning in her own tears, Alice finds she still doesn't fit in here in Wonderland--when she grows bigger than a house! What's a size-challenged girl to do? Consult a caterpillar, of course! Following its dubious advice, she heads off to the forest. There she encounters the Cheshire Cat, who could point her to the right path--if he weren't insane...
name: Advice from a Caterpillar

description: SIEGE BLOCKBUSTER TIE-IN!! PART 3 OF 3! Daken has been given glimpses of the life he could have-as well as the lives he might destroy-and the time for a choice is finally at hand. Will he become a force for good...or reign as a king in Hell?
name: Godlike Conclusion

description: SIEGE BLOCKBUSTER TIE-IN!! Back in DARK AVENGERS/UNCANNY X-MEN:UTOPIA, Dani Moonstar made a deal with Hela. Now, the mistress of Hel is calling in her marker. With all the Asgardians falling in the Siege of Asgard, someone needs to deal with the dead. And who better to do so than a Valkyrie. But where is Dani supposed to be bringing these dead? Brought to you by a guest creative team of Kieron Gillen (THOR, S.W.O.R.D.) and Niko Henrichon (PRIDE OF BAGHDAD).
name: Hel's Valkyrie

description: Things are never what they seem in Wonderland. A chance meeting with a Cheshire Cat takes Alice to teatime at the Mad Hatters, where she is the guest of the hour! She then finds herself further honored by attending a weird croquet match and being introduced to the dangerously temperamental Queen of Hearts!
